<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1004,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1580,1606]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[439,512,1581,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[439,512,1581,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Meges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[706,863,1580,1607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="225 - 336" refId="ref5958" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) Longicornia Malayana; or, a descriptive catalogue of the species of the three longicorn families Lamiidae, Cerambycidae and Prionidae, collected by Mr. A. R. Wallace in the Malay Archipelago. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, (3) 3, 225 - 336." type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe (1866)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<taxonomicName authority="Pascoe, 1858" authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1858" box="[906,1314,1580,1607]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monochamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravidus">
<emphasis box="[906,1160,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Monochamus gravidus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pascoe F. P." box="[1165,1314,1580,1607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="236 - 266" refId="ref5891" refString="Pascoe F. P. (1858) On new genera and species of longicorn Coleoptera. Part III. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, (2) 4 (6 - 7), 236 - 266, pls XXV, XXVI. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1858. tb 01823. x" type="journal article" year="1858">Pascoe, 1858</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Clermont, 1932" authorityName="Clermont" authorityYear="1932" box="[151,446,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Magninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,260,1617,1642]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Magninia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Clermont, J." box="[269,446,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="214 - 216" refId="ref5650" refString="Clermont, J. (1932) Description d'un genre et d'une espece nouveaux de Cerambycidae de la sous-famille des Lamiinae [Col.]. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 37 (15), 214 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1932.14460" type="journal article" year="1932">Clermont, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was established based on 
<taxonomicName authority="Clermont, 1932" authorityName="Clermont" authorityYear="1932" box="[750,1075,1616,1642]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Magninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinea">
<emphasis box="[750,885,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">M. tonkinea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Clermont, J." box="[895,1075,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="214 - 216" refId="ref5650" refString="Clermont, J. (1932) Description d'un genre et d'une espece nouveaux de Cerambycidae de la sous-famille des Lamiinae [Col.]. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 37 (15), 214 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1932.14460" type="journal article" year="1932">Clermont, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Clermont, J." box="[1088,1277,1616,1642]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="214 - 216" refId="ref5650" refString="Clermont, J. (1932) Description d'un genre et d'une espece nouveaux de Cerambycidae de la sous-famille des Lamiinae [Col.]. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 37 (15), 214 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1932.14460" type="journal article" year="1932">Clermont (1932)</bibRefCitation>
differentiated this genus from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[332,405,1653,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[332,405,1653,1678]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Meges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by “les deux sillons oculaires” (“the two eye furrows”, meaning uncertain) less oblique, the scutellum more widely rounded and frons with a pair of deep comma-shaped dimple anteriorly (=pretentorial pit). 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[151,337,1724,1750]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="281 - 512" refId="ref5611" refString="Breuning, S. (1944) Etudes sur les Lamiaires (Coleop. Cerambycidae). Douzieme tribu: Agniini Thomson. Novitates Entomologicae, 3 eme supplement (107 - 135), 281 - 512." type="book chapter" year="1944">Breuning (1944)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName authority="Pascoe, 1866" authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[499,726,1724,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[499,572,1725,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Meges</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[579,726,1724,1751]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="225 - 336" refId="ref5958" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) Longicornia Malayana; or, a descriptive catalogue of the species of the three longicorn families Lamiidae, Cerambycidae and Prionidae, collected by Mr. A. R. Wallace in the Malay Archipelago. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, (3) 3, 225 - 336." type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe, 1866</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName authority="Dejean, 1821" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" box="[789,1095,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monochamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[789,940,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Monochamus</emphasis>
Dejean, 1821
</taxonomicName>
without providing any reason, but retained 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clermont" authorityYear="1932" box="[294,403,1761,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Magninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,403,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Magninia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid. In his key, 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[640,827,1760,1786]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="281 - 512" refId="ref5611" refString="Breuning, S. (1944) Etudes sur les Lamiaires (Coleop. Cerambycidae). Douzieme tribu: Agniini Thomson. Novitates Entomologicae, 3 eme supplement (107 - 135), 281 - 512." type="book chapter" year="1944">Breuning (1944)</bibRefCitation>
separated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clermont" authorityYear="1932" box="[949,1058,1761,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Magninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[949,1058,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Magninia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" box="[1129,1280,1760,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monochamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1129,1280,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Monochamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly by its elytra provided with humeral spines. However, based on the comparison of high-quality photographs of the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1797,1823]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">type</typeStatus>
specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1858" box="[303,558,1832,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monochamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravidus">
<emphasis box="[303,558,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Monochamus gravidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Clermont" authorityYear="1932" box="[611,822,1832,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Magninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tonkinea">
<emphasis box="[611,822,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Magninia tonkinea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and the investigation of fresh material of both species, no significant difference can be found to support their generic separation, especially regarding the considerable similarities of their endophallic structures (
<figureCitation box="[633,712,1904,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–5" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1179,1203]" captionTargetBox="[161,1429,278,1136]" captionTargetId="figure-74@3.[151,1436,270,1153]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–5. Male habitus of Meges spp. and Pseudomeges spp. 1, Meges gravidus (Pascoe, 1858) from Hangzhou City, Zhejiang, China; 2, M. tonkineus (Clermont, 1932) from Ledong County, Hainan, China; 3, Pseudomeges marmoratus (Westwood, 1848) from Motuo County, Xizang, China; 4, P. aureus Bi, Chen &amp; Lin sp. nov. from Pingbian County, Yunnan, China; 5 Pseudomeges varioti Le Moult, 1946 from Chiang Mai, Thailand." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6389230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6389230/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Figs. 5</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[724,740,1904,1931]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–7" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1132,1156]" captionTargetBox="[165,1415,196,1090]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[151,1436,181,1108]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 6–7. Habitus and labels of the holotype of species. 6, Monohammus gravidus Pascoe, 1858; 7, Magninia tonkinea Clermont, 1932." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6389234" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6389234/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">6</figureCitation>
). Therefore, 
<taxonomicName authority="Clermont, 1932" authorityName="Clermont" authorityYear="1932" box="[886,1177,1904,1930]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Magninia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[886,995,1905,1930]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Magninia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Clermont, J." box="[1001,1177,1904,1930]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="214 - 216" refId="ref5650" refString="Clermont, J. (1932) Description d'un genre et d'une espece nouveaux de Cerambycidae de la sous-famille des Lamiinae [Col.]. Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France, 37 (15), 214 - 216. https: // doi. org / 10.3406 / bsef. 1932.14460" type="journal article" year="1932">Clermont, 1932</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is herein synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authority="Pascoe, 1866" authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[208,439,1940,1967]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[208,281,1941,1966]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Meges</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pascoe, F. P." box="[288,439,1940,1967]" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" pagination="225 - 336" refId="ref5958" refString="Pascoe, F. P. (1866) Longicornia Malayana; or, a descriptive catalogue of the species of the three longicorn families Lamiidae, Cerambycidae and Prionidae, collected by Mr. A. R. Wallace in the Malay Archipelago. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, (3) 3, 225 - 336." type="journal article" year="1866">Pascoe, 1866</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1004,2039]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,609]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">
In addition, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[453,526,1977,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[453,526,1977,2002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Meges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is proposed herein to be resurrected from synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Dejean, 1821" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monochamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1191,1342,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="243">Monochamus</emphasis>
Dejean, 1821
</taxonomicName>
by combination of the following characters: body stout, antennae relatively short, pronotal lateral spines long and sharp, curved backwards, elytra carinated, elytral apices spined, protibia with a subapical tooth beneath, male endophallus with cs highly reduced or nearly absent, MPH without significant swelling or protuberance, PB provided with sf and si, and APH provided apically with a pair of rod-like sclerites associated with the ejaculatory ducts. While in 
<taxonomicName authority="sutor (Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="sutor (Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[338,711,258,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monochamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sutor" subSpecies="sutor">
<emphasis box="[338,361,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[379,504,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">sutor sutor</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1758)
</taxonomicName>
, the 
<typeStatus box="[771,819,259,285]" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1821" box="[954,1105,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monochamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[954,1105,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">Monochamus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, body relatively slender and antennae relatively long, pronotal lateral spines less acute apically and not curved, elytra without carinae, elytral apices rounded, protibia untoothed, male endophallus with cs well developed, MPH swollen near middle and apex, PB lacking sf and si, and APH provided with a single V-shaped sclerite.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,609]" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">
<bibRefCitation author="Pascoe F. P." box="[199,358,402,429]" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" pagination="236 - 266" refId="ref5891" refString="Pascoe F. P. (1858) On new genera and species of longicorn Coleoptera. Part III. The Transactions of the Entomological Society of London, (2) 4 (6 - 7), 236 - 266, pls XXV, XXVI. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1858. tb 01823. x" type="journal article" year="1858">Pascoe (1858)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned the similarities between his 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1858" box="[803,1059,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Monochamus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gravidus">
<emphasis box="[803,1059,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">Monochamus gravidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Westwood, 1848" authorityName="Westwood" authorityYear="1848" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Hammaticherus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marmoratus">
<emphasis box="[1113,1436,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">Hammaticherus marmoratus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Westwood, J. O." box="[151,339,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" refId="ref6116" refString="Westwood, J. O. (1848) The cabinet of oriental entomology; being a selection of rare and beautiful insects, natives of India and the adjacent islands. W. Smith, London ii + 88 pp., 42 pls. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 34273" type="book" year="1848">Westwood, 1848</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(the 
<typeStatus box="[396,444,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Breuning, 1944" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1944" box="[569,906,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudomeges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[569,721,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">Pseudomeges</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[728,906,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" pagination="281 - 512" refId="ref5611" refString="Breuning, S. (1944) Etudes sur les Lamiaires (Coleop. Cerambycidae). Douzieme tribu: Agniini Thomson. Novitates Entomologicae, 3 eme supplement (107 - 135), 281 - 512." type="book chapter" year="1944">Breuning, 1944</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). Based on the comparison of both 
<typeStatus box="[1300,1348,439,465]" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">type</typeStatus>
species in this study, the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pascoe" authorityYear="1866" box="[412,485,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[412,485,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">Meges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1944" box="[787,939,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Pseudomeges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[787,939,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="244">Pseudomeges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the antennal scape with the cicatrix more prominent and delimited by a distinct carina (“scape provided with a complete cicatrix” in 
<bibRefCitation author="Breuning, S." box="[1173,1344,511,537]" pageId="2" pageNumber="244" pagination="137 - 280" refId="ref5572" refString="Breuning, S. (1943) Etudes sur les Lamiaires (Coleop. Cerambycidae). Douzieme tribu: Agniini Thomson. Novitates Entomologicae, 3 eme supplement (89 - 106), 137 - 280." type="book chapter" year="1943">Breuning 1943</bibRefCitation>
), elytral apices provided with long sutural spine, protibia with a subapical tooth beneath, male endophallus with the MPH relatively longer and slenderer.
</paragraph>
